	<h2>Privacy notice statement</h2>
	<p>Public Services and Procurement Canada and the Contract Security Program respect the personal privacy of individuals who visit their websites.</p>
	<h3>Collecting personal information</h3>
	<p>The Contract Security Program does not automatically gather any personal information from you during your visit to its websites.</p>
	<p>Any personal information you provide to the program is voluntary. This may include your name, telephone number, email or street address. The program protects and uses your information per the federal <a href="http://laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/p-21/"><cite>Privacy Act</cite></a> and <a href="http://www.tbs-sct.gc.ca/pol/doc-eng.aspx?id=12510"><cite>Policy on Privacy Protection</cite></a>. The program will tell you when and why your personal information is being collected, and that you have a right to access this information.</p>
	<h3>Identifying unauthorized access</h3>
	<p>The Contract Security Program monitors network traffic to identify unauthorized access. It uses software to identify attempts to upload or change information or to cause damage.</p>
	<p>This program’s software receives and records the <abbr title="Internet Protocol">IP</abbr> address of any computer contacting the website, the date and time of the visit and the pages visited. The program will never identify users by their <abbr title="Internet Protocol">IP</abbr> address unless it detects an attempt to damage the website.</p>
	<h3>Improving web efficiency</h3>
	<p>The Contract Security Program may sometimes use cookies to track how visitors use this website and to determine which websites were previously visited.</p>
	<p>Cookies are files that may be placed on your hard drive without your knowledge by a website to allow it to monitor your use of the website. They do not allow the Contract Security Program to identify individuals. Instead, they are compiled as data on web traffic patterns and are used to assess the program’s website efficiency. If a website is using cookies that collects personal information, an on-screen notice will let you know that this is happening. You can refuse to allow cookies. If you do, the website will work the same way and you will still have access to the same information.</p>
